Furthermore, grounding knowledge from KGs to pre-train LMs has shown improvements in performance on generation and QA tasks [Chen2020KGPTKP, Ribeiro2020InvestigatingPL, Ouz2020UniKQAUR]. In another approach, [verga2020facts] proposed an interpretable neuro-symbolic KB, where the memory consists of vector representations of entities and relations from an existing KB. These representations are augmented to an LM during pre-training and fine-tuning, enabling the model to excel in knowledge-intensive QA tasks.